WorkItem.Description:
When editing an item using the provided EditTextBox control, if the binding is not set with UpdateSourceTrigger=PropertyChanged, then it is never updated. 

My current workaround is to add the following method override in EditTextBox.cs. It's a bit hackish but it works, so you can use it if you want.

```
protected override void OnLostKeyboardFocus(KeyboardFocusChangedEventArgs e)
{
    BindingExpression be = GetBindingExpression(TextProperty);
    if (be != null)
        be.UpdateSource();
}
```

Also, beside this issue, I noted the following inconsistency:

```
case Key.Escape:
    StopEditing();
    e.Handled = true;
        break;
case Key.Return:
    FocusHelper.Focus(this);
    IsEditing = false;
    e.Handled = true;
        break;
```

When the key is Return, StopEditing() is not invoked, I believe it should be.
